H0.text: the part of the cytoskeleton made from the protein actin is called. Actin Fiber

H1.text: the part of the cytoskeleton made from the protein actin is called. Cytoskeletal Rod

H2.text: the part of the cytoskeleton made from the protein actin is called. Actin Strand

H3.text: the part of the cytoskeleton made from the protein actin is called. microfilament

A4.text: Measuring approximately 7 nm in diameter, microfilaments are the thinnest fibers of the cytoskeleton.

A5.text: Actin filaments (also known as microfilaments) are protein filaments in the cytoplasm of eukaryotic cells that form part of the cytoskeleton.
